Questions:
What are the alternative options available to a patient who chooses not to participate in the PK Analysis of Antitumor B study for oral cancer?
A) Undergoing a different type of surgery not related to oral cancer; 
B) Participating in another research project, receiving routine care, or opting for no treatment at all; 
C) Immediate enrollment in a long-term oral cancer treatment program; 
D) Receiving a placebo instead of the study compound ATB.

Correct answer: B

If you experience an injury related to the research study, whom should you contact immediately?

A) The MCW/Froedtert Hospital Research Subject Advocate;
B) The Principal Investigator, Stuart Wong, MD;
C) The U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA);
D) Your personal physician.

Correct answer: B) The Principal Investigator, Stuart Wong, MD.
